# 4.3 Installation de Docker

Installez Docker selon la procédure fournie : 

# 1. Installation Docker CE (méthode officielle)

## 1.1 Supprimer les paquets en conflit

```
sudo apt remove docker.io docker-compose docker-compose-v2 docker-doc podman-docker containerd runc
```

## 1.2 Installer les prérequis

```sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y ca-certificates curl
```

## 1.3 Ajouter la clé GPG

```sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
sudo curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
```

## 1.4 Ajouter le dépôt

```echo   "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu   $(. /etc/os-release && echo "${UBUNTU_CODENAME:-$VERSION_CODENAME}") stable" |   sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
```

## 1.5 Installer Docker

```sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin
```

## 1.6 Vérification

```sudo systemctl status docker
docker --version
docker compose version
```
